{% extends "@core/docs/_layout.twig" %}

{% block doc_content %}
    <h1>Console Commands</h1>
    <p>
        Rhapsody includes a powerful CLI tool to help you with common development and maintenance tasks. You can run it with <code>php rhapsody</code> followed by the command name. For a quick list, type:
    </p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody list</code></pre>

    <h2>Application Commands</h2>

    <h3><code>app:cache-warm</code></h3>
    <p>Pre‑compiles all Twig templates for faster production performance.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody app:cache-warm</code></pre>

    <h3><code>cache:clear</code></h3>
    <p>Clears the application cache (Twig cache, route cache, and OPcache if enabled).</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody cache:clear</code></pre>

    <h3><code>env:sync</code></h3>
    <p>Adds any missing environment variables from <code>.env.example</code> to your <code>.env</code> file without overwriting existing values.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody env:sync</code></pre>

    <h3><code>route:cache</code></h3>
    <p>Compiles all route definitions into a cached PHP file for faster routing.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody route:cache</code></pre>

    <h3><code>route:clear</code></h3>
    <p>Removes the route cache file.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody route:clear</code></pre>

    <hr>

    <h2>Code Generation Commands</h2>
    <p>These commands help you quickly generate boilerplate code for your application.</p>

    <h3><code>make:controller</code></h3>
    <p>Create a new controller class.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody make:controller UserController</code></pre>

    <h3><code>make:model</code></h3>
    <p>Create a new model class.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody make:model Post</code></pre>

    <h3><code>make:middleware</code></h3>
    <p>Create a new middleware class.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody make:middleware CheckAdmin</code></pre>

    <h3><code>make:event</code></h3>
    <p>Create a new event class.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody make:event OrderShipped</code></pre>

    <h3><code>make:listener</code></h3>
    <p>Create a new listener class.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody make:listener SendOrderConfirmation</code></pre>

    <h3><code>make:migration</code></h3>
    <p>Create a new database migration.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody make:migration create_posts_table</code></pre>

    <h3><code>migrate</code></h3>
    <p>Run all pending migrations.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody migrate</code></pre>

    <hr>

    <h2>Version & Update Commands</h2>

    <h3><code>check-version</code></h3>
    <p>Check if a newer version of the framework is available.</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody check-version</code></pre>

    <h3><code>update</code></h3>
    <p>Update the framework to the latest version (if using Composer).</p>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">php rhapsody update</code></pre>

    <hr>

    <div class="bg-yellow-100 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 text-yellow-700 p-4">
        <strong>Tip:</strong> Use <code>php rhapsody help [command]</code> to see detailed help for any command, e.g., <code>php rhapsody help make:controller</code>.
    </div>
{% endblock %}